Answer: The member of the Birmingham Press Club who re-examined the Lindbergh kidnapping case is:
\begin{blockquote}
John F. Condon
\end{blockquote}
John F. Condon, a journalist and former member of the Birmingham Press Club, reopened the Lindbergh case in 1932 and, after a thorough investigation, identified the kidnapper as Bruno Hauptmann. Condon's work led to Hauptmann's arrest, trial, and execution for the crime.
